==Events== *[[1294]] &ndash; [[Pope Celestine V|Saint Celestine V]] [[papal resignation|resigns]] the [[Pope|papacy]] after only five months to return to his previous life as an [[Asceticism|ascetic]] [[hermit]]. *[[1545]] &ndash; The [[Council of Trent]] begins. *[[1577]] &ndash; Sir [[Francis Drake]] sets sail from [[Plymouth]], England, on his round-the-world voyage. *[[1636]] &ndash; The [[Massachusetts Bay Colony]] organizes three [[militia]] regiments to defend the colony against the [[Pequot people|Pequot]] [[Native Americans in the United States|Indians]]. This organization is recognized today as the founding of the [[National Guard of the United States]]. *[[1642]] &ndash; [[Abel Tasman]] is the first recorded European to sight New Zealand. *[[1643]] &ndash; [[English Civil War]]: The [[Battle of Alton]] takes place in [[Hampshire]]. *[[1758]] &ndash; The English transport ship ''[[Duke William (ship)|Duke William]]'' sinks in the North Atlantic, killing over 360 people. *[[1769]] &ndash; [[Dartmouth College]] is founded by the Reverend [[Eleazar Wheelock]], with a [[royal charter]] from King [[George III of the United Kingdom|George III]], on land donated by [[Governor-general#British colonialism and the governors-general|Royal governor]] [[Sir John Wentworth, 1st Baronet|John Wentworth]]. *[[1818]] &ndash; [[Cyril VI of Constantinople]] resigns from his position as Ecumenical Patriarch. *[[1862]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: At the [[Battle of Fredericksburg]], [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]] General [[Robert E. Lee]] defeats [[Union Army|Union]] Major General [[Ambrose Burnside]]. *[[1867]] &ndash; A [[Fenian]] bomb explodes in [[Clerkenwell]], London, killing six. *[[1928]] &ndash; [[George Gershwin]]'s ''[[An American in Paris]]'' is first performed. *[[1936]] &ndash; An [[Solar eclipse of December 13, 1936|annular solar eclipse]] occurred and was visible from Australia, New Zealand on December 14th (Monday), and Oeno Island in Pitcairn Islands on December 13th (Sunday).<ref>{{cite web |url = https://eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov/5MCSE/TP2009-214174.pdf |title = Five Millennium Catalog of Solar Eclipses:–1999 to +3000 (2000 BCE to 3000 CE)—Revised |website=eclipse.gsfc.nasa.gov |language=en |access-date=2020-01-01 }}</ref> *[[1937]] &ndash; [[Second Sino-Japanese War]]: [[Battle of Nanking]]: The city of [[Nanjing]], defended by the [[National Revolutionary Army]] under the command of General [[Tang Shengzhi]], falls to the [[Empire of Japan|Japanese]]. This is followed by the [[Nanking Massacre]], in which Japanese troops rape and slaughter hundreds of thousands of civilians. *[[1938]] &ndash; [[The Holocaust]]: The [[Neuengamme concentration camp]] opens in the [[Bergedorf]] district of [[Hamburg]], Germany. *[[1939]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: [[Battle of the River Plate]]: Captain [[Hans Langsdorff]] of the [[Nazi Germany|German]] [[Deutschland-class cruiser]] (pocket battleship) ''[[German cruiser Admiral Graf Spee|Admiral Graf Spee]]'' engages with [[Royal Navy]] cruisers {{HMS|Exeter|68|6}}, {{HMS|Ajax|22|6}} and {{HMS|Achilles|70|6}}. *[[1943]] &ndash; World War II: The [[Massacre of Kalavryta]] by German occupying forces in Greece. *[[1949]] &ndash; The [[Knesset]] votes to move the capital of [[Israel]] to [[Jerusalem]]. *[[1959]] &ndash; [[List of archbishops of Cyprus|Archbishop]] [[Makarios III]] becomes the first [[President of Cyprus]]. *[[1960]] &ndash; While [[Emperor of Ethiopia|Emperor]] [[Haile Selassie]] of [[Ethiopia]] visits Brazil, his [[Kebur Zabagna|Imperial Bodyguard]] [[1960 Ethiopian coup attempt|seizes the capital]] and proclaims him deposed and his son, Crown Prince [[Amha Selassie|Asfa Wossen]], Emperor. *[[1962]] &ndash; [[NASA]] launches ''[[Relay program#Relay 1|Relay 1]]'', the first active repeater communications [[satellite]] in orbit. *[[1967]] &ndash; [[Constantine II of Greece]] attempts an unsuccessful [[Greek military junta of 1967–74#The King's counter-coup|counter-coup]] against the [[Greek military junta of 1967–74|Regime of the Colonels]]. *[[1968]] &ndash; Brazilian President [[Artur da Costa e Silva]] issues [[AI-5]] (Institutional Act No. 5), enabling government by decree and suspending [[habeas corpus]]. *[[1972]] &ndash; [[Apollo program]]: [[Eugene Cernan]] and [[Harrison Schmitt]] begin the third and final [[extra-vehicular activity]] (EVA) or "Moonwalk" of ''[[Apollo 17]]''. To date they are the last humans to set foot on the Moon. *[[1974]] &ndash; [[Malta]] becomes a republic within the [[Commonwealth of Nations]]. *[[1977]] &ndash; [[Air Indiana Flight 216]] crashes near [[Evansville Regional Airport]], killing 29, including the [[Evansville Purple Aces men's basketball|University of Evansville basketball team]], support staff, and boosters of the team. *[[1981]] &ndash; General [[Wojciech Jaruzelski]] declares [[martial law]] in Poland, largely due to the actions by ''[[Solidarity (Polish trade union)|Solidarity]]''. *[[1982]] &ndash; The 6.0 {{M|s}} [[1982 North Yemen earthquake|North Yemen earthquake]] shakes southwestern [[Yemen]] with a maximum [[Mercalli intensity scale|Mercalli intensity]] of VIII (''Severe''), killing 2,800, and injuring 1,500. *[[1988]] &ndash; [[Chairman of the Palestine Liberation Organization|PLO Chairman]] [[Yasser Arafat]] gives a speech at a [[United Nations General Assembly|UN General Assembly]] meeting in [[Geneva]], Switzerland, after United States authorities refused to grant him a [[Visa (document)|visa]] to visit UN headquarters in New York. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[The Troubles]]: [[Attack on Derryard checkpoint]]: The [[Provisional Irish Republican Army]] launches an attack on a [[British Army]] temporary vehicle checkpoint near [[Rosslea|Rosslea, Northern Ireland]]. Two British soldiers are killed and two others are wounded. *[[2001]] &ndash; [[Sansad Bhavan]], the building housing the [[Parliament of India|Indian Parliament]], [[2001 Indian Parliament attack|is attacked by terrorists]]. Twelve people are killed, including the terrorists. *[[2002]] &ndash; [[2004 enlargement of the European Union|European Union enlargement]]: The EU announces that [[Cyprus]], the [[Czech Republic]], [[Estonia]], [[Hungary]], [[Latvia]], [[Lithuania]], [[Malta]], [[Poland]], [[Slovakia]], and [[Slovenia]] will become members on May 1, 2004. *[[2003]] &ndash; [[Iraq War]]: [[Operation Red Dawn]]: Former Iraqi President [[Saddam Hussein]] is captured near his home town of [[Tikrit]]. *[[2007]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of Lisbon]] is signed by members states of the [[European Union]]. *[[2011]] &ndash; A [[2011 Liège attack|murder–suicide]] in [[Liège]], Belgium, kills six and wounds 125 people at a [[Christmas market]]. *[[2018]] &ndash; A high-speed train crashes in [[Ankara]], Turkey, killing at least nine people and injuring 84.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/12/13/world/europe/turkey-train-crash.html|title=Train Crash in Ankara, Turkey, Kills at Least 9 and Injures Dozens|newspaper=The New York Times|access-date=2018-12-15}}</ref>
